# llm-wiki-bootstrap (Cursor rules)

This project is an `llm-wiki-bootstrap` instance — a personal LLM-wiki knowledge base operated via five named workflows.

## Read this first

**`AGENTS.md`** at the project root is the canonical schema. It defines the three-layer model (raw / wiki / schema), page conventions, link convention, raw source frontmatter spec, and the five workflows. Read it before doing any work in this directory.

## Three-layer model

- `raw/` — immutable source material curated by the user. **You may only read it.**
- `wiki/` — LLM-owned markdown pages. **You are the sole writer.** The user does not edit `wiki/*.md` directly.
- `AGENTS.md` — the schema. User and you co-evolve it.

## Five workflows

The same five operations exist as Claude Code slash commands at `.claude/commands/wiki-*.md`. In Cursor, invoke them by natural language ("run the wiki-ingest workflow") — the prompt body of each command file is the workflow definition; follow it step-by-step.

| Workflow | What it does | Trigger |
|---|---|---|
| `wiki-init` | Scaffold an empty wiki structure (idempotent). | User asks to "initialize the wiki." |
| `wiki-extract <source>` | Acquire a URL / file / image into `raw/` with frontmatter. Does not touch `wiki/`. | User asks to "fetch X into raw." |
| `wiki-ingest [<raw-file>]` | Run the 7-step pipeline from `wiki/ingest-pipeline.md`. Use `scripts/body-hash.sh` for delta detection. | User asks to "ingest" / "process raw" / "update the wiki." |
| `wiki-query <question>` | Answer from `wiki/`; web-search and auto-promote new knowledge on gaps. `--visual [html\|pdf\|png]` also emits a diagram of the answer (archetype auto-picked from the query). | User asks any substantive question about the wiki's domain. |
| `wiki-lint` | Find broken links, orphans, contradictions, stale claims, gaps. Reports by default; applies under `--apply`. | User asks to "lint" / "check the wiki" / "find issues." |

Plus two **output workflows** that render/export an already-built wiki. They are read-only on `raw/` and `wiki/` (write only new output artifacts) and sit outside the five-command lifecycle loop:

| Workflow | What it does | Trigger |
|---|---|---|
| `wiki-visualize [graph\|mermaid\|slides\|serve] [target]` | Render the wiki as a D3 graph (default), MARP slides, or mermaid images, or serve it locally. Wraps `scripts/visualize/*`. Mechanical — renders existing structure. | User asks to "visualize" / "graph" / "show the wiki." |
| `wiki-flashcards [dir]` | Export `## Flashcards` sections to an Anki-importable CSV. Wraps `scripts/wiki-to-anki.sh`. | User asks to "export flashcards" / "make an Anki deck." |
| `wiki-diagram "<intent>"` | Semantic — retrieve relevant pages, score the 8 archetypes (`templates/infographic/`), user picks, generate a self-contained HTML poster to `diagrams/`. Wiki-read-only. | User asks for "a diagram of X for <audience>" / "infographic" / "show the status of X." |

## Hard rules

1. **Never write to `raw/`.** You may only edit the `ingested_hash`, `ingested_at`, and `ingested_pages` fields in raw frontmatter — and only as the last step of `wiki-ingest`.
2. **Use `scripts/body-hash.sh`** to compute the canonical body hash. Do not reinvent this with inline `sha256sum` / `shasum` — different invocations produce different hashes and break idempotence.
3. **Pure CommonMark.** No Obsidian callouts (`> [!note]`), no dataview blocks, no Cursor-specific markdown, no embeds. The wiki must render identically in `cat`, GitHub web, VSCode preview, or anywhere else.
4. **Always cite raw sources** with `(source: raw/<file>#<anchor>)` for any non-trivial claim in a wiki page.
5. **Append a log.md entry** for every `wiki-ingest`, `wiki-query` promotion, or `wiki-lint --apply` you perform.

## Frontmatter spec (recap from AGENTS.md)

Every wiki page:
```yaml
title: <Title>
type: concept | entity | summary | analysis | navigation
source: video | analysis | external | mixed
updated: YYYY-MM-DD
tags: [...]
```

Every raw source:
```yaml
source_url: <url|n/a>
source_type: <video-transcript | article | image | ...>
source_title: "..."
source_author: "..."
fetched_at: YYYY-MM-DD
ingested_hash: ""
ingested_at: never
ingested_pages: []
```

## When in doubt

Read `AGENTS.md`. Then read `wiki/index.md`.
